<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,1333,1790]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1333,1358]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Skeleton robust, Body stellate, marginal plates form distinct frame around edge (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1307,1333,1358]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,230,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[151,1435,230,1851]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 15. Goniodiscaster aegis n. sp. Holotype, USNM E51097. R=4.7, r=1.9 cm. A. Abactinal surface. Scale bar=1.0 cm. B. Closeup of abactinal surface with white box around interradial paired plates and “fold”. Scale bar=0.3 cm. C. Interradius showing superomarginal and inferomarginal plates.Scale bar=0.5 cm. D. Actinal surface. Scale bar=1.0 cm. E. Closeup of furrow and adambulacral spines. Scale bar =0.3 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615956/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 15A</figureCitation>
). Abactinal plates abutted, covered by continuous granular cover (
<figureCitation box="[776,880,1369,1394]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,230,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[151,1435,230,1851]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 15. Goniodiscaster aegis n. sp. Holotype, USNM E51097. R=4.7, r=1.9 cm. A. Abactinal surface. Scale bar=1.0 cm. B. Closeup of abactinal surface with white box around interradial paired plates and “fold”. Scale bar=0.3 cm. C. Interradius showing superomarginal and inferomarginal plates.Scale bar=0.5 cm. D. Actinal surface. Scale bar=1.0 cm. E. Closeup of furrow and adambulacral spines. Scale bar =0.3 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615956/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 15B</figureCitation>
). Interradial regions with paired abactinal plates forming distinct “fold” in each interradius (
<figureCitation box="[659,764,1405,1430]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,230,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[151,1435,230,1851]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 15. Goniodiscaster aegis n. sp. Holotype, USNM E51097. R=4.7, r=1.9 cm. A. Abactinal surface. Scale bar=1.0 cm. B. Closeup of abactinal surface with white box around interradial paired plates and “fold”. Scale bar=0.3 cm. C. Interradius showing superomarginal and inferomarginal plates.Scale bar=0.5 cm. D. Actinal surface. Scale bar=1.0 cm. E. Closeup of furrow and adambulacral spines. Scale bar =0.3 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615956/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 15B</figureCitation>
). Spines and/or tubercles present or absent. Marginal and actinal surface covered by granular cover. Pedicellariae absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,1333,1790]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1477,1502]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Comments.</emphasis>
It is argued herein that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1909" box="[600,771,1477,1502]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Goniodiscaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[600,771,1477,1502]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Goniodiscaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares more characters with the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mah &amp; Foltz" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1137,1296,1477,1502]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
, specifically the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fisher" authorityYear="1919" box="[197,365,1513,1538]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Anthenoidinae">Anthenoidinae</taxonomicName>
, such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perrier" authorityYear="1881" box="[482,620,1513,1538]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Anthenoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[482,620,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Anthenoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and similar genera such as 
<emphasis box="[970,1202,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Ogmaster, Stellaster</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dollfus" authorityYear="1936" box="[1268,1429,1513,1538]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Stellasteropsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1268,1429,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Stellasteropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1909" box="[151,322,1549,1574]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Goniodiscaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,322,1549,1574]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Goniodiscaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the more flattened body form, but also the interradial paired plates present in the interradii, and the distinct “fold” created by their contact (
<figureCitation box="[689,788,1585,1610]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,230,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[151,1435,230,1851]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 15. Goniodiscaster aegis n. sp. Holotype, USNM E51097. R=4.7, r=1.9 cm. A. Abactinal surface. Scale bar=1.0 cm. B. Closeup of abactinal surface with white box around interradial paired plates and “fold”. Scale bar=0.3 cm. C. Interradius showing superomarginal and inferomarginal plates.Scale bar=0.5 cm. D. Actinal surface. Scale bar=1.0 cm. E. Closeup of furrow and adambulacral spines. Scale bar =0.3 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615956/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 15B</figureCitation>
) which I argue are synapomorphies for this group. A full summary of this group is premature and beyond the scope of this treatment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,1333,1790]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1909" box="[199,370,1657,1682]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Goniodiscaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,370,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Goniodiscaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally assigned to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mah &amp; Foltz" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[717,873,1657,1682]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, H. L." box="[914,1116,1657,1682]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="107 - 135" refId="ref69330" refString="Clark, H. L. (1909) Notes on some Australian and Indo-Pacific echinoderms. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard, 52, 107 - 135." type="journal article" year="1909">H.L. Clark (1909)</bibRefCitation>
and retained there by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fisher, W. K." pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 547" refId="ref70312" refString="Fisher, W. K. (1919) Starfishes of the Philippine seas and adjacent waters. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 3 (100), 1 - 547, 156 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.1126 / science. 50.1293.348" type="book chapter" year="1919">Fisher (1919)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. M. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E." box="[287,566,1693,1718]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" refId="ref69107" refString="Clark, A. M. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E. (1971) Monograph of Shallow-water Indo-West Pacific Echinoderms. British Museum (Natural History) Publications 690. British Museum (Natural History), London, ix + 238, 31 pls." type="book" year="1971">Clark and Rowe (1971)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Doderlein, L." box="[580,777,1693,1718]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="71 - 110" refId="ref69939" refString="Doderlein, L. (1935) Die Asteriden der Siboga-Expedition. III. Oreasteridae. Siboga-Expedition, 46 (2), 71 - 110, pls. 15 - 20. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11319" type="journal article" year="1935">Döderlein (1935)</bibRefCitation>
moved 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1909" box="[875,1046,1693,1718]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Goniodiscaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[875,1046,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Goniodiscaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the 
<taxonomicName box="[1134,1278,1693,1718]" class="Asteroidea" family="Oreasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Oreasteridae</taxonomicName>
, where it has remained in most contemporary summary treatments and checklists (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer, W. K. &amp; Wright, C. K." box="[1009,1290,1729,1754]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="4 - 107" refId="ref74422" refString="Spencer, W. K. &amp; Wright, C. K. (1966) Asterozoans, Part U: Echinodermata. In: Moore, R. C. (Ed.), Treatise on Invertebrate Paleontology, 3 (1). University of Kansas Press, Lawrence, 4 - 107. [U 4 - U 107]" type="book chapter" year="1966">Spencer &amp; Wright 1966</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. M." pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="187 - 366" refId="ref69077" refString="Clark, A. M. (1993) An index of names of recent Asteroidea-Part 2: Valvatida. E chinoderm Studies, 4, 187 - 366." type="journal article" year="1993">A.M. Clark 1993</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rowe, F. W. E. &amp; Gates, J." box="[221,453,1765,1790]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 510" refId="ref73976" refString="Rowe, F. W. E. &amp; Gates, J. (1995) Echinodermata. In: Wells, A. (Ed.), Zoological Catalogue of Australia. Fol. 33. CSIRO, Melbourne, pp. 1 - 510. https: // doi. org / 10.1086 / 419606" type="book chapter" year="1995">Gates &amp; Rowe 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
